Properties.Description:
An estimate of an individual's true breeding value for a trait based on the performance of the individual and close relatives for the trait.

EBV is a systematic way of combining available performance information on the individual brothers and sisters and the progeny of the individual.

Breeding values are calculated using information which is collected by farmers, on-farm. 

Ex:
- Herd Testing data
- Weighing data
- Body Condition Scores 
- 'Traits other than production' scores
